WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:14.324 --> 01:15.408
You're late.

01:19.287 --> 01:20.747
I feel like

01:22.415 --> 01:24.417
I'm constantly letting you down.

01:29.088 --> 01:31.090
If you're talking about standing me up,

01:31.174 --> 01:32.217
you're right.

01:33.927 --> 01:36.930
But you're making it hard for me
to get angry at you.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.807
I'm sorry.

01:43.812 --> 01:45.063
Did something happen?

01:47.398 --> 01:48.525
I have a favor to ask.

01:50.026 --> 01:53.029
Please don't come to the office
for some time

01:54.781 --> 01:56.199
without asking me why.

01:59.327 --> 02:01.037
I'm so sorry…

02:04.833 --> 02:06.292
I couldn't make it today.

02:34.904 --> 02:36.990
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

02:45.039 --> 02:46.833
I-rang didn't come home yesterday?

02:46.916 --> 02:48.543
It doesn't seem so.

02:49.210 --> 02:50.962
Maybe a new ghost came.

02:51.045 --> 02:52.630
A new ghost came?

02:53.923 --> 02:56.050
I was away from the office
a few days for acting jobs.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.510
It's just my guess.

02:59.095 --> 03:00.805
Don't worry too much.

03:00.889 --> 03:01.931
I'll check on him later.

03:03.141 --> 03:04.976
Would you like a cup of tea?

03:16.821 --> 03:17.989
LEAVE OUR SCHOOL!
I-RANG'S DAD, UGH!

03:18.823 --> 03:19.908
I-RANG'S DAD IS A CRIMINAL!

03:36.799 --> 03:37.800
Are you okay?

03:40.428 --> 03:43.223
Do you not have a home? Or…

03:46.517 --> 03:47.518
were you kicked out?

03:48.102 --> 03:49.854
It's none of your business.

03:49.938 --> 03:52.565
You tossed and turned
in a cold sweat all night.

03:52.649 --> 03:55.735
I was worried you were
going through something bad.

04:00.114 --> 04:01.824
Haven't you ever thought

04:01.908 --> 04:04.160
it's all because of you?

04:04.244 --> 04:05.328
What do you mean?

04:05.411 --> 04:08.623
How can I possibly have a good sleep
when a ghost is watching me?

04:09.499 --> 04:10.500
Oh.

04:11.501 --> 04:13.586
Now that you know, please go away.

04:14.128 --> 04:15.213
Anywhere is fine

04:16.005 --> 04:17.382
as long as I don't have to see you.

04:24.597 --> 04:27.016
If you don't mind,

04:27.767 --> 04:29.310
may I ask why?

04:32.855 --> 04:34.732
Because you don't convince me.

04:35.358 --> 04:38.319
How can an attorney do their job
if they aren't convinced by their client?

04:40.113 --> 04:41.197
Attorney

04:42.156 --> 04:43.157
and client?

04:45.076 --> 04:46.995
Do you perhaps know who I am?

04:48.329 --> 04:50.248
Of course not.

04:50.999 --> 04:55.211
I'm saying
you don't look convincing at all.

04:56.337 --> 04:58.965
It's not right
to judge a book by its cover.

04:59.048 --> 05:02.593
Especially, legal professionals
must not have prejudice and bias.

05:02.677 --> 05:06.222
They must treat everyone justly and fairly

05:06.306 --> 05:08.558
without any kind of discrimination.

05:13.104 --> 05:14.564
Says someone who did the opposite.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.620
Who did the opposite?

05:31.414 --> 05:33.291
Why doesn't he want me in the office?

05:39.338 --> 05:41.049
Does he feel uncomfortable seeing me?

05:46.471 --> 05:47.847
SUBMIT YOON JAE-UK CASE MATERIALS
TO COURT

05:52.351 --> 05:53.603
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

05:59.650 --> 06:00.735
Hello, Attorney Shin.

06:02.236 --> 06:05.615
I'm calling because we have to submit
Mr. Yoon's case materials today.

06:07.742 --> 06:08.743
I…

06:09.535 --> 06:10.953
forgot to tell you

06:11.954 --> 06:12.997
but…

06:14.207 --> 06:15.833
we're not taking on that case.

06:16.417 --> 06:17.418
What?

06:18.169 --> 06:19.170
Why?

06:21.047 --> 06:24.425
Did a new ghost come or something?

06:25.927 --> 06:26.928
Attorney Han.

06:28.262 --> 06:30.223
I'm a little busy right now.

06:31.057 --> 06:32.058
Oh.

06:32.892 --> 06:34.060
Okay.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.397
What on earth is going on?

06:48.574 --> 06:49.742
The court building is…

06:52.286 --> 06:53.496
very close to here.

06:54.705 --> 06:56.707
It must be convenient for work.

06:57.542 --> 06:58.709
Why now?

07:04.674 --> 07:06.926
-Excuse me?
-Why does it have to be now?

07:08.761 --> 07:10.638
Because of you, I…

07:17.562 --> 07:18.980
Oh, I'm sorry.

07:19.063 --> 07:20.982
Are you consulting with a client?

07:21.065 --> 07:23.151
No, it's nothing.

07:25.611 --> 07:27.530
Well, aren't you hungry?

07:27.613 --> 07:30.324
Your mom packed some gimbap for you.

07:30.908 --> 07:33.286
Anyway, did Attorney Han go somewhere?

07:33.369 --> 07:35.288
Mom's gimbap?

07:36.122 --> 07:38.499
Wow, it smells so savory.

07:38.583 --> 07:39.917
It smells savory.

07:41.377 --> 07:43.212
Try this.

07:43.296 --> 07:44.338
Here you go.

07:46.257 --> 07:47.967
-You want some too?
-Sure.

07:50.052 --> 07:51.053
Sa-rang, you too.

07:52.013 --> 07:54.640
Your egg gimbap is indeed

07:55.183 --> 07:56.559
one of a kind.

07:56.642 --> 07:57.643
It is.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.605
Bong-su, wait.

08:01.230 --> 08:03.232
I'm not hungry right now.
I'll have this later.

08:04.775 --> 08:07.361
And if I happen to get possessed,

08:07.445 --> 08:09.530
splash water on me right away.

08:09.614 --> 08:10.615
Okay?

08:11.491 --> 08:13.743
Don't hesitate, and do it straightaway.

08:13.826 --> 08:14.827
Okay.

08:14.911 --> 08:18.581
Goodness. I get it. Don't worry.

08:18.664 --> 08:19.665
Oh, right.

08:20.458 --> 08:22.919
Your mom's very worried.

08:24.212 --> 08:27.924
If you're sleeping or eating
without any problems…

08:28.466 --> 08:32.595
Parents are constantly worried
when their children aren't around.

08:42.355 --> 08:43.481
Bong-su.

08:45.399 --> 08:46.651
The truth is…

08:47.318 --> 08:49.820
What is it? Got something to tell me?

08:53.241 --> 08:56.452
Go ahead and tell me.
You know I'm tight-lipped.

08:59.664 --> 09:00.665
I'm not?

09:02.875 --> 09:06.254
Anyway, give your mother a call
while we're at it.

09:06.337 --> 09:08.339
She's been worried since this morning.

09:08.422 --> 09:09.465
Okay.

09:16.389 --> 09:19.517
I didn't have any at home
to have some with you here.

09:29.569 --> 09:32.280
Who can possibly resist this aroma?

09:48.713 --> 09:50.047
Um…

09:50.131 --> 09:51.257
Excuse me.

09:52.425 --> 09:54.594
I'm not usually one to be rude,

09:54.677 --> 09:57.305
but this aroma is

09:57.388 --> 09:58.973
just irresistible.

09:59.056 --> 10:00.766
If you don't mind,

10:00.850 --> 10:04.353
may I have a little?
Just a little, please.

10:06.480 --> 10:08.357
Sure.

10:08.441 --> 10:10.234
Of course, you may.

10:10.318 --> 10:11.611
Oh.

10:11.694 --> 10:14.155
I'm the paralegal here.

10:15.823 --> 10:18.117
Thank you, Mr. Paralegal.

10:18.200 --> 10:20.244
-Have a seat.
-Thank you.

10:22.622 --> 10:23.706
Water.

10:32.381 --> 10:34.717
It's better to die full than live hungry.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.762
I wake him after he's eaten.

10:43.184 --> 10:45.478
Here. Have some water too.

10:46.270 --> 10:49.106
It makes no sense.
How can something be this delicious?

10:50.858 --> 10:52.276
Is it that good?

10:52.943 --> 10:54.153
It's amazing.

11:01.869 --> 11:03.037
How should I put it?

11:04.080 --> 11:05.122
For some reason,

11:06.290 --> 11:09.877
it even tugs at my heartstrings.

11:10.378 --> 11:14.507
My mother-in-law's cooking is to die for…

11:14.590 --> 11:16.592
I mean, to live for.

11:17.134 --> 11:19.011
-Help yourself.
-Yes, thank you.

11:19.095 --> 11:20.596
I'll help myself.

11:20.679 --> 11:22.515
Oh, I have some soup too.

11:42.410 --> 11:44.954
Hi, Prosecutor Kim.
I'm calling to ask you something.

11:45.663 --> 11:48.541
Do you know why
Mr. Yoon changed attorneys?

11:49.583 --> 11:52.586
I'm guessing you heard something
since you're in charge of the case.

11:53.170 --> 11:55.005
I haven't heard anything,
but I have a hunch.

11:55.089 --> 11:59.093
His father, Mr. Yoon Dae-myeong,
was involved in a case 20 years ago.

11:59.176 --> 12:02.555
The prosecutor in charge was Shin Gi-jung.

12:03.431 --> 12:04.765
Attorney Shin's father.

12:07.101 --> 12:08.102
Really?

12:12.106 --> 12:13.357
So?

12:15.651 --> 12:16.861
I'm home.

12:16.944 --> 12:17.945
Hey.

12:19.405 --> 12:22.241
So, how is I-rang?

12:22.324 --> 12:24.118
He's well.

12:24.201 --> 12:26.704
And he does have a new ghost client.

12:27.288 --> 12:30.416
I guess he isn't
on good terms with that ghost, though.

12:30.499 --> 12:32.668
He wants me to wake him up
as soon as he gets possessed.

12:33.252 --> 12:34.962
Why? What kind of ghost is it?

12:35.671 --> 12:38.257
I-rang said it was a woman in her sixties,

12:38.340 --> 12:40.926
but it sounded like a man
when he was possessed.

12:41.844 --> 12:43.804
You're probably mistaken.

12:44.388 --> 12:47.016
Anyway, I saw I-rang say
something strange to the ghost.

12:47.099 --> 12:48.225
Like what?

12:48.809 --> 12:50.811
Like, "Because of you, I"…

12:50.895 --> 12:54.899
It sounded like he was, let me say…

12:54.982 --> 12:56.150
resentful.

13:01.322 --> 13:03.908
BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

13:10.206 --> 13:12.666
Did I-rang have this lunch box?

13:12.750 --> 13:14.627
Yes. Actually, no.

13:14.710 --> 13:16.003
The possessed I-rang did.

13:17.671 --> 13:19.381
Tell me more about that ghost.

13:19.465 --> 13:20.633
The ghost?

13:21.383 --> 13:23.594
Oh, she loved your egg gimbap.

13:24.303 --> 13:25.888
-What else?
-More?

13:25.971 --> 13:28.974
He was very polite and sounded gentle.

13:29.058 --> 13:30.059
Why do you ask?

13:31.477 --> 13:32.978
No, nothing.

13:33.062 --> 13:35.856
-Oh, let me get ready at the restaurant.
-Okay.

13:52.873 --> 13:56.585
Geez. I told him to wake me up right away.

14:04.176 --> 14:07.012
How long have you
been living this kind of life?

14:08.931 --> 14:10.975
-What?
-How many ghosts

14:11.850 --> 14:13.519
have you gone through?

14:13.602 --> 14:14.979
Why are you curious?

14:15.062 --> 14:17.398
It must've been very hard.

14:18.065 --> 14:20.359
It may have been dangerous at times.

14:20.442 --> 14:21.443
That's right.

14:22.194 --> 14:23.696
I almost got into an accident.

14:24.280 --> 14:25.573
I almost got killed too.

14:25.656 --> 14:27.700
Still, you didn't stop?

14:29.326 --> 14:32.580
They clung to me all the time like this.
How was I supposed to stop?

14:35.040 --> 14:36.417
I see you are…

14:38.419 --> 14:39.670
a good man.

14:42.214 --> 14:43.674
I'm just a softy.

14:44.967 --> 14:48.470
That's why I'm dealing with you even now.

14:50.222 --> 14:51.473
From now on,

14:53.183 --> 14:54.602
I plan to be heartless.

15:05.446 --> 15:06.447
Look.

15:06.947 --> 15:09.909
Do any of these talismans
draw strongly to you?

15:10.659 --> 15:12.703
A talisman that draws to me?

15:45.486 --> 15:46.528
Hello, Father.

15:47.154 --> 15:50.199
I'm calling about a ghost
who needs to pass on.

15:51.116 --> 15:53.327
No, right away today.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.497
If you're busy, I'll go to you.

16:03.045 --> 16:05.047
I tell you to pass on,
but you wouldn't listen.

16:06.090 --> 16:07.800
I'll have to send you off myself.

16:57.474 --> 17:00.185
Did you make up your mind to send me off?

17:04.898 --> 17:07.401
Yes, I'm going to do so.

17:09.570 --> 17:11.447
You seem to resent me a lot.

17:24.793 --> 17:26.712
I have no idea about myself

17:27.421 --> 17:29.381
except for the fact that I'm dead.

17:31.050 --> 17:33.802
So, I can neither reflect on myself
nor apologize.

17:47.066 --> 17:49.151
Have you experienced this before?

17:50.110 --> 17:53.739
Did you ever send away a ghost
without telling them who they were?

18:01.038 --> 18:02.539
Was I that evil?

18:04.208 --> 18:06.502
Enough for you to not tell me who I am…

18:06.585 --> 18:07.961
Was I that nasty?

18:10.464 --> 18:11.965
Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung

18:12.633 --> 18:14.676
used my father as a sacrificial lamb.

18:16.095 --> 18:17.763
For his own good,

18:18.931 --> 18:20.182
he drove my father

18:22.017 --> 18:24.061
to death.

18:26.355 --> 18:27.356
Yes.

18:30.067 --> 18:32.486
You are someone who can never be forgiven.

18:34.863 --> 18:37.366
You deceived those who trusted you.

18:38.826 --> 18:40.786
You framed an innocent person

18:40.869 --> 18:42.496
and wrecked his family.

18:44.373 --> 18:46.667
He died because of you!

18:48.293 --> 18:49.628
And those who survived

18:50.838 --> 18:52.589
suffered in pain for a long time.

18:52.673 --> 18:54.842
After doing something so despicable…

18:57.094 --> 18:59.513
you died without a single apology.

19:07.813 --> 19:11.733
Be grateful that
I'm not telling you who you are.

19:13.652 --> 19:14.736
If I did,

19:16.488 --> 19:18.907
you'd want to die again out of shame.

20:01.283 --> 20:02.701
Oh, no!

20:04.286 --> 20:06.622
-Geez.
-I win!

20:06.705 --> 20:07.706
Gosh.

20:07.789 --> 20:11.126
I'm no longer a match for you
when it comes to games now.

20:12.669 --> 20:15.255
But I'm better than you at running.

20:17.799 --> 20:19.509
Whoever gets home first wins. Ready, go!

20:20.802 --> 20:22.721
Dad, that's cheap!

20:52.125 --> 20:55.087
HAPPY, FUN, AND FRIENDLY TODAY
JUST LIKE YESTERDAY

20:56.964 --> 20:58.966
I-rang, watch.

20:59.549 --> 21:02.761
To throw a fastball,
put your index and middle fingers together

21:02.844 --> 21:04.137
like this

21:05.555 --> 21:07.557
and push it out as you release.

21:12.729 --> 21:14.606
-Like this?
-That's right.

21:15.232 --> 21:16.358
Give it a try.

21:18.568 --> 21:19.736
Dad.

21:20.320 --> 21:22.197
I don't think I can do this.

21:22.281 --> 21:24.616
When you aren't sure about yourself,

21:25.284 --> 21:28.620
take a deep breath and think to yourself
that you can do it.

21:28.704 --> 21:31.540
It will bring you real courage.

21:38.547 --> 21:39.756
I can do it.

21:40.257 --> 21:41.258
All right.

21:48.473 --> 21:49.683
Not bad.

21:50.225 --> 21:53.603
It went a little off,
but I could see it spinning clearly.

21:54.813 --> 21:56.148
Good job, I-rang.

21:59.860 --> 22:00.861
One more time.

22:21.798 --> 22:23.091
Why did you do that back then?

22:24.468 --> 22:25.469
Excuse me?

22:25.552 --> 22:27.054
Who on earth is the man

22:28.388 --> 22:29.639
I remember?

22:32.476 --> 22:34.519
You left of your own accord.

22:35.729 --> 22:37.314
Now, you show up however you please. Why?

22:38.815 --> 22:40.358
I've been trying

22:40.442 --> 22:43.028
so hard to forget you.

22:46.406 --> 22:48.575
Don't approach me with that clueless look

22:49.951 --> 22:51.161
on your face.

22:58.251 --> 22:59.878
I'll stop now.

23:07.844 --> 23:10.722
I won't try to find out who I am.

23:12.307 --> 23:13.683
To be honest,

23:13.767 --> 23:15.811
it's hard to understand.

23:16.853 --> 23:19.272
I don't know who I am
nor do I have any memory,

23:20.816 --> 23:23.443
but it's difficult to accept
that I lived that way

23:24.611 --> 23:26.404
when I was still alive.

23:26.488 --> 23:29.783
So that's why I wanted to know
how I lived even more.

23:31.034 --> 23:32.035
But now,

23:33.036 --> 23:34.830
I'll believe what you say.

23:36.873 --> 23:38.250
You are…

23:54.266 --> 23:57.227
a very decent man.

23:58.979 --> 24:01.356
I got to have conversations,
thanks to you.

24:01.439 --> 24:03.859
Even now, you're torn if it's right

24:04.401 --> 24:05.694
to send me away.

24:07.654 --> 24:10.115
I'm okay no matter what you decide.

24:11.700 --> 24:13.243
I'm very sorry…

24:15.537 --> 24:17.455
for showing up out of the blue.

24:45.400 --> 24:46.776
Don't resent me.

24:55.660 --> 24:58.663
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

25:30.028 --> 25:31.071
I'm home.

25:33.490 --> 25:35.116
What about the ghost?

25:35.909 --> 25:36.910
What?

25:37.869 --> 25:40.413
Oh, I mean…

25:41.206 --> 25:43.792
Bong-su told me
you got a new ghost client.

25:44.793 --> 25:47.045
Oh, he…

25:49.714 --> 25:50.715
He left.

25:55.512 --> 25:57.472
-He left?
-Yes.

25:59.599 --> 26:01.059
He wanted to leave,

26:02.894 --> 26:04.938
so I just let him.

26:11.069 --> 26:12.362
So you did.

26:14.864 --> 26:16.074
Mom.

26:22.247 --> 26:24.624
I couldn't sleep much yesterday.

26:24.708 --> 26:27.294
I see. Go on and rest up.

28:10.230 --> 28:11.689
Thank you for making time.

28:16.778 --> 28:18.363
Until a few days ago,

28:18.988 --> 28:22.784
you didn't know Attorney Shin's father
was Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung.

28:23.868 --> 28:25.662
How did you find out about it?

28:27.831 --> 28:30.041
I got a text from an unknown number.

28:32.544 --> 28:34.921
Attorney Shin must be here.

28:39.884 --> 28:41.094
DO NOT TRUST SHIN I-RANG.

28:41.177 --> 28:43.304
HIS FATHER IS THE CORRUPT
PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG

28:43.388 --> 28:44.681
WHO DROVE YOUR FATHER TO DEATH.

28:46.516 --> 28:48.977
It ended 20 years ago anyway.

28:49.060 --> 28:50.687
I don't want to bother with it anymore.

28:51.312 --> 28:53.481
I read the articles from that time.

28:54.149 --> 28:55.859
You didn't accept

28:55.942 --> 29:00.071
that your father committed suicide.

29:00.947 --> 29:02.365
My father habitually said

29:03.533 --> 29:05.952
that one needed to be responsible
for their actions.

29:07.495 --> 29:10.165
All his life, he followed that conviction.

29:10.749 --> 29:12.250
A man like him commit suicide?

29:14.335 --> 29:15.670
It makes no sense.

29:16.337 --> 29:19.841
Do you still have the records?

29:21.426 --> 29:22.510
I do.

29:23.636 --> 29:25.764
But it's too late to do anything now.

29:25.847 --> 29:27.348
It's been 22 years.

29:27.432 --> 29:29.309
Because it's been that long.

29:32.103 --> 29:33.188
I know it's late,

29:34.105 --> 29:36.149
but shouldn't we reveal the truth?

29:36.232 --> 29:39.444
Why are you so engrossed with this case?

29:46.493 --> 29:49.954
Losing family and being unable to grieve

29:50.705 --> 29:52.624
is something I know all too well.

29:55.376 --> 29:57.504
I know someone who's just like you.

30:02.926 --> 30:03.927
Huh?

30:04.552 --> 30:06.262
Why are you up?

30:06.346 --> 30:08.515
I couldn't sleep.

30:09.140 --> 30:10.225
Why are you up?

30:11.810 --> 30:13.728
I'm preparing for tomorrow's business.

30:29.077 --> 30:30.119
What is it?

30:31.204 --> 30:32.539
Do you have something to tell me?

30:33.248 --> 30:34.249
No.

30:37.460 --> 30:40.880
How come you never left this neighborhood?

30:42.799 --> 30:44.092
This whole area

30:44.884 --> 30:47.178
is full of those who called Dad names.

30:48.012 --> 30:50.181
I've always wondered why

30:51.432 --> 30:52.892
you ran the restaurant here.

30:58.648 --> 31:00.400
Leaving here…

31:01.943 --> 31:03.903
felt like losing.

31:05.446 --> 31:09.200
I didn't want to admit
that your dad was an evil man.

31:10.994 --> 31:13.580
I thought the truth
would be revealed someday

31:15.415 --> 31:18.418
and that I'd hold out until then.

31:20.837 --> 31:21.838
So you…

31:24.048 --> 31:26.050
had faith in Dad.

31:28.386 --> 31:29.804
That's right.

31:34.350 --> 31:38.021
But that's just what I think.

31:38.563 --> 31:42.108
Even if you think otherwise,

31:42.817 --> 31:44.861
I understand and respect you.

32:51.177 --> 32:53.888
LAW OFFICE

33:03.022 --> 33:04.983
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

33:35.763 --> 33:37.223
Attorney Han.

33:53.364 --> 33:54.824
It's about your father, isn't it?

33:57.744 --> 33:59.662
How did you know?

33:59.746 --> 34:01.539
Prosecutor Kim told me

34:01.622 --> 34:06.210
that your father was related
to Mr. Yoon's father's case.

34:08.212 --> 34:10.840
I talked to Mr. Yoon in person too.

34:13.551 --> 34:14.552
I'm sorry.

34:15.219 --> 34:16.471
I nosed around without asking.

34:18.264 --> 34:19.265
Don't say that.

34:20.058 --> 34:22.351
It's my fault for not opening up to you.

34:23.853 --> 34:26.564
I should've told you sooner.

34:28.941 --> 34:30.568
Attorney Shin, for me…

34:32.195 --> 34:33.279
what I want to say is…

34:35.406 --> 34:37.200
don't push yourself too hard for me.

34:38.951 --> 34:42.789
You can take your time and tell me later
when you feel more at ease.

34:48.669 --> 34:50.505
But do me just one thing.

34:51.589 --> 34:53.633
Let me stay by your side.

34:55.051 --> 34:57.178
For what you did about my sister and all,

34:57.261 --> 34:59.555
I owe you a lot, you know.

35:00.807 --> 35:01.808
Thanks.

35:04.352 --> 35:06.896
I won't forget how grateful I am.

35:07.605 --> 35:09.357
Stop it now.

35:09.440 --> 35:11.400
You might end up spoiling me.

35:14.737 --> 35:16.656
I want to keep that promise.

35:17.907 --> 35:19.742
So help me out and let me.

35:40.054 --> 35:42.348
Mr. Chairman,
Attorney Shin I-rang is here to see you.

35:42.932 --> 35:46.018
He didn't make an appointment, but
he says you'll let him in if I tell you.

35:47.395 --> 35:48.729
Let him in.

35:49.397 --> 35:50.439
Yes, sir.

36:03.286 --> 36:07.165
I came to ask you about my father.

36:08.624 --> 36:09.625
Your father?

36:10.459 --> 36:14.213
For all this time,
I didn't try to look into him.

36:15.256 --> 36:17.049
I was curious at times,

36:17.800 --> 36:19.760
but I forced myself not to be curious.

36:21.012 --> 36:22.221
But now,

36:23.848 --> 36:25.391
I want to know.

36:28.895 --> 36:31.105
You take after him the more I see you.

36:33.608 --> 36:34.609
Do I?

36:38.446 --> 36:40.406
Your firm and upright eyes

36:41.157 --> 36:42.450
are quite like his.

36:47.705 --> 36:50.041
I tried to look into the cases
he worked on,

36:50.124 --> 36:51.417
but it wasn't easy.

36:52.043 --> 36:54.629
It was after I resigned
from the prosecution,

36:56.005 --> 36:58.216
and the prosecutors were
very hostile toward him.

36:58.299 --> 37:00.218
They weren't willing to cooperate at all.

37:02.595 --> 37:03.596
But…

37:05.139 --> 37:07.808
I had a hunch about this case
from a long time ago.

37:12.104 --> 37:15.066
It was when your father worked
at the Incheon Prosecutors' Office.

37:18.110 --> 37:20.905
We used to meet up and talk about life
from time to time.

37:21.822 --> 37:24.742
That day, he seemed somewhat different.

37:26.577 --> 37:27.578
Byung-il.

37:28.496 --> 37:29.497
What?

37:31.123 --> 37:32.124
Never mind.

37:34.418 --> 37:36.462
Don't leave me hanging like that.

37:36.545 --> 37:37.964
What is it? Tell me.

37:41.133 --> 37:43.177
I'm not sure if I'm doing the right thing.

37:43.970 --> 37:46.430
I just have to redress an injustice.

37:47.515 --> 37:48.641
But oddly,

37:50.017 --> 37:51.352
something feels off.

37:52.812 --> 37:53.854
Prosecutor Shin.

37:54.438 --> 37:56.148
It will all pass eventually.

37:57.108 --> 37:59.568
What can you do? Just forget it.

38:05.116 --> 38:07.576
When was that?

38:07.660 --> 38:11.455
It must've been right before
he arrested the gangsters in Chinatown.

38:13.666 --> 38:15.042
Chinatown…

38:15.835 --> 38:16.961
My father

38:17.044 --> 38:20.047
was found dead in the back alley
of Chinatown in Incheon.

38:23.509 --> 38:24.510
What's wrong?

38:24.593 --> 38:27.596
I think I should visit
the Incheon Prosecutors' Office.

38:29.015 --> 38:31.350
It's been 20 years now.
I doubt you'll find anything there.

38:32.351 --> 38:34.562
No one there will even remember Gi-jung.

38:34.645 --> 38:35.646
Besides…

38:37.732 --> 38:39.984
if anyone does remember him,

38:40.067 --> 38:41.569
it may be hard to gain cooperation.

38:44.864 --> 38:46.449
But maybe if it's a cop…

38:48.492 --> 38:49.535
A cop?

38:51.245 --> 38:53.372
Corporal Choi Dong-man.

38:53.456 --> 38:56.042
He's a detective that has worked
in Chinatown for a long time.

38:56.625 --> 38:58.878
He might know something.

38:59.545 --> 39:01.255
Corporal Choi Dong-man…

39:04.508 --> 39:05.634
Thank you, sir.

39:11.057 --> 39:12.183
Gi-jung was…

39:13.893 --> 39:15.853
one of my closest juniors.

39:16.896 --> 39:20.649
Make sure to let me know
if anything new comes up.

39:22.360 --> 39:24.195
Okay, I will.

39:34.955 --> 39:35.956
Gi-jung was…

39:36.791 --> 39:38.584
one of my closest juniors.

39:39.668 --> 39:43.714
Make sure to let me know
if anything new comes up.

39:56.102 --> 39:57.103
Hello, sir.

39:57.186 --> 39:59.563
Where are you? I need to see you.

39:59.647 --> 40:00.815
Do you mean now, sir?

40:04.193 --> 40:05.194
Yes, sir.

40:06.821 --> 40:08.030
Hurry over here.

40:27.091 --> 40:28.259
So…

40:28.968 --> 40:30.386
if a ghost

40:30.928 --> 40:35.850
left Okcheon Building
without regaining their memory,

40:36.600 --> 40:38.519
where would they go?

40:41.939 --> 40:46.110
Where a ghost would go with no memory?

40:49.864 --> 40:51.866
From my experience,

40:51.949 --> 40:54.827
ghosts made a strong reaction

40:55.703 --> 40:58.581
to their favorite food or music
or the people they loved.

40:59.582 --> 41:00.708
In this case,

41:01.292 --> 41:05.880
they may be drawn
to certain places as well.

41:05.963 --> 41:08.382
-A certain place?
-Yes.

41:09.049 --> 41:12.553
Someplace where their hearts remember,

41:12.636 --> 41:13.929
not their heads.

41:22.021 --> 41:26.358
AT WOLMIDO IN 1984

41:33.282 --> 41:35.242
A little more. Just a little more, okay?

41:49.924 --> 41:51.509
Mom, are you going somewhere?

41:52.092 --> 41:54.929
Oh. I have somewhere to be.

41:55.513 --> 41:58.182
I see. Have a safe trip.

41:58.265 --> 41:59.266
Okay.

42:00.851 --> 42:02.645
So, did you find the shaman?

42:03.145 --> 42:05.439
Please wait a little.
I'll be able to find him soon.

42:06.106 --> 42:07.733
You also know

42:08.400 --> 42:11.070
that my father is excessively reticent.

42:11.779 --> 42:13.155
Still, this is wrong.

42:15.157 --> 42:16.367
Are you trying to lecture me?

42:18.035 --> 42:20.538
You don't realize
the grim reality of the situation.

42:29.129 --> 42:31.632
Apparently, my father
didn't make a full recovery.

42:36.387 --> 42:37.721
In this situation,

42:38.305 --> 42:40.015
what do you think you should do?

42:40.641 --> 42:42.768
Who do you think
you should be listening to?

42:51.527 --> 42:52.778
What is it that you want?

42:55.239 --> 42:57.324
Tell me everything that my father knows

42:57.408 --> 42:59.243
from start to finish.

43:01.745 --> 43:02.746
It started

43:03.455 --> 43:06.292
when Attorney Han Na-hyun lost a case
against Shin I-rang.

43:06.375 --> 43:07.376
Hey, punk.

43:07.918 --> 43:10.296
Are you out of your goddamn mind?

43:10.379 --> 43:13.757
You're running your mouth
because you see nothing, aren't you?

43:15.092 --> 43:17.761
As a series of unexplainable incidents
indicated that he saw ghosts,

43:17.845 --> 43:21.432
the Chairman kept an eye on Shin I-rang.

43:22.182 --> 43:25.978
He knew from the beginning
that Shin I-rang could see ghosts.

43:29.648 --> 43:32.401
Is that enough of a reason for him
to stop treatment and come back to Korea?

43:32.484 --> 43:36.155
At first, the Chairman simply thought
Shin I-rang was an oddball.

43:37.239 --> 43:38.240
But…

43:38.782 --> 43:41.493
when he found out that
he was Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung's son,

43:41.577 --> 43:42.745
he came straight back.

43:45.831 --> 43:50.210
He came back in case Shin I-rang sees
Shin Gi-jung's spirit?

43:51.003 --> 43:52.004
That's right.

44:25.579 --> 44:27.039
SEOIN KENDO CLUB

44:52.064 --> 44:53.148
Come on, man.

44:54.483 --> 44:56.318
Are you happy
that you knocked your senior out?

45:07.704 --> 45:10.416
Why does my father
bother with this dead man?

45:10.499 --> 45:11.583
That,

45:12.584 --> 45:13.669
I'm not sure.

45:16.004 --> 45:17.005
And then?

45:19.633 --> 45:21.009
After returning to Korea,

45:21.677 --> 45:23.971
the Chairman wanted me
to find the missing male shaman.

45:26.807 --> 45:27.975
The male shaman?

45:30.727 --> 45:32.187
So, did you find him?

45:35.858 --> 45:37.693
Did you find him or not?

45:48.454 --> 45:51.999
My father worked
at the Incheon Prosecutors' Office.

45:52.666 --> 45:54.793
He investigated a case about Chinatown.

45:56.462 --> 45:59.715
You'll get to hear some details
about your father soon.

46:00.299 --> 46:04.052
First, I'm going to meet a detective
who knows about my father's case.

46:09.558 --> 46:10.976
Thanks for calling me.

46:11.602 --> 46:12.644
I know it wasn't easy.

46:14.480 --> 46:16.190
You told me not to be alone.

46:49.097 --> 46:51.934
Goodness. Gi-jung, stop filming now.

46:52.017 --> 46:53.268
-Gyeong-hwa.
-Yes?

46:53.810 --> 46:56.480
Seeing you through the lens
with one eye closed,

46:57.272 --> 46:58.857
you look even prettier, so I can't stop.

47:00.359 --> 47:02.194
A little more. Just a little more, okay?

47:03.445 --> 47:04.530
Oh, boy.

47:05.948 --> 47:06.949
A bit to the left.

47:07.032 --> 47:09.076
-The left?
-Yes, a bit to the left.

47:09.159 --> 47:10.160
-Okay.
-Wait.

47:10.244 --> 47:12.788
-A bit to the back from there.
-To the back?

47:13.413 --> 47:15.707
Oh, my! It's cold!

47:15.791 --> 47:17.793
My goodness!

47:19.628 --> 47:20.629
Gi-jung.

47:21.255 --> 47:22.548
That was intentional, wasn't it?

47:22.631 --> 47:24.383
No, it wasn't.

47:24.466 --> 47:26.176
It was intentional. I can tell.

47:26.260 --> 47:28.679
-No, earlier… No, it wasn't.
-Come here.

47:28.762 --> 47:30.097
-No.
-Gi-jung, come here.

47:30.597 --> 47:33.684
-I didn't mean it. I…
-Come here. Stop running away.

47:33.767 --> 47:35.227
No, I…

47:46.405 --> 47:49.283
I had so much to tell you.

47:56.873 --> 47:58.083
Still…

48:00.544 --> 48:02.421
thank you for coming.

48:30.032 --> 48:31.199
Where is this place?

48:56.683 --> 48:58.644
Please let me go.

49:00.062 --> 49:03.148
I told you all that I knew.

49:11.531 --> 49:13.659
INCHEON CENTRAL POLICE DEPARTMENT

49:13.742 --> 49:16.953
Corporal Choi retired
and went to his hometown last year.

49:17.037 --> 49:19.623
Oh, I see.

49:20.582 --> 49:24.252
There's someone who might know well
about the Four Dragons Gang.

49:25.545 --> 49:26.588
Who…

49:26.672 --> 49:28.465
He's a fixture in Chinatown.

49:33.053 --> 49:35.514
THE RED HOUSE

49:36.848 --> 49:37.849
The Four Dragons Gang?

49:38.392 --> 49:42.396
Yes, it was a gang that infested
this neighborhood 20 years ago.

49:42.479 --> 49:46.233
Why are you looking for the gangsters
who were dismantled a long time ago?

49:48.193 --> 49:50.570
It involves my family.

49:51.279 --> 49:52.572
Please tell me.

49:53.323 --> 49:54.324
Well,

49:55.075 --> 49:56.076
it's the same old story.

49:56.952 --> 50:01.164
They were parasites sucking the lifeblood
out of small business owners here.

50:02.833 --> 50:05.544
They demanded half of all profits
in exchange for protection.

50:06.461 --> 50:08.088
They messed with those who refused

50:09.131 --> 50:11.508
and ruined their businesses
by making fake complaints.

50:13.677 --> 50:15.053
They were vicious.

50:16.430 --> 50:17.597
Like vipers.

50:20.851 --> 50:24.146
How did they end up falling apart?

50:24.646 --> 50:25.981
One day,

50:26.773 --> 50:28.275
that man came.

50:34.823 --> 50:38.827
A righteous and flawless prosecutor.

50:39.411 --> 50:40.454
Arrest them all.

50:40.537 --> 50:41.997
Boys, let's go!

50:51.381 --> 50:52.632
-Get off me.
-Move!

50:53.341 --> 50:58.555
The bribes they offered him
backfired right back at them.

50:59.181 --> 51:02.934
He was such an upstanding gentleman.

51:05.812 --> 51:08.690
We finally got to breathe thanks to him.

51:10.025 --> 51:13.195
To us, he's our savior.

51:20.118 --> 51:21.912
I know it's been a long time,

51:21.995 --> 51:24.706
but do you perhaps remember his name?

51:26.583 --> 51:27.918
I used to know.

51:28.001 --> 51:29.252
Goodness.

51:29.336 --> 51:31.421
What was his name…

51:32.047 --> 51:34.382
Could it be Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung?

51:34.466 --> 51:35.717
Shin Gi-jung?

51:37.135 --> 51:40.972
Don't even bring up that crook's name.

51:41.556 --> 51:44.851
That bastard was a shady prosecutor

51:44.935 --> 51:47.979
who sucked up to the Four Dragons Gang
for his own gains.

51:48.730 --> 51:49.898
No.

51:49.981 --> 51:51.900
I wouldn't even call him a prosecutor.

51:51.983 --> 51:54.569
He was a total thug.

51:54.653 --> 51:56.404
-Goodbye, sir.
-Goodbye, sir.

51:56.488 --> 51:57.614
All right.

51:58.406 --> 52:00.992
Hey, dress a bit spiffier, okay?

52:01.743 --> 52:05.580
Hey, punk. Don't wear something so shiny.

52:09.459 --> 52:10.460
Oh, gosh.

52:12.879 --> 52:14.589
How much are you loading up?

52:15.674 --> 52:17.092
Even two cakes?

52:17.175 --> 52:18.468
Take one for yourselves.

52:18.552 --> 52:19.553
Thank you, sir.

52:20.387 --> 52:23.390
The police walked on eggshells around him.

52:23.473 --> 52:26.685
Under his protection,
the gang grew bigger and bigger.

52:30.939 --> 52:32.649
The business owners here

52:32.732 --> 52:37.279
still shudder at the very thought of him.

52:38.280 --> 52:41.908
He was… awfully despicable.

52:41.992 --> 52:43.159
Geez.

52:44.786 --> 52:45.787
Ugh.

52:48.373 --> 52:50.375
THE RED HOUSE

52:54.796 --> 52:57.048
The righteous prosecutor's name is…

52:57.132 --> 52:58.592
I'm moving, geez!

52:58.675 --> 53:00.719
My wrists hurt, man!

53:02.095 --> 53:04.306
…Prosecutor Yang Byung-il.

53:23.241 --> 53:25.452
I told you everything I knew.

53:26.161 --> 53:27.287
So…

53:27.370 --> 53:30.624
Can you please let me go now?

53:30.707 --> 53:31.708
One more thing.

53:33.627 --> 53:36.713
What should be done to get rid of a ghost?

53:36.796 --> 53:38.381
Burn it.

53:39.341 --> 53:42.344
Burn their talisman,
and the ghost will disappear.

53:46.473 --> 53:47.599
Does the Chairman know this?

53:51.436 --> 53:52.771
Does he know?

53:54.397 --> 53:55.649
Yes, he does.

54:05.575 --> 54:07.035
Shin I-rang came by.

54:07.118 --> 54:08.119
So?

54:08.662 --> 54:10.789
We did as you said, sir.

54:11.331 --> 54:12.415
Good job.

54:20.090 --> 54:27.097
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

54:32.936 --> 54:34.479
-Today--
-Thank you

54:35.397 --> 54:36.690
for accompanying me

54:37.691 --> 54:38.692
today.

54:41.569 --> 54:43.321
You must be tired. Get some rest.

54:48.326 --> 54:49.494
You too.

56:03.193 --> 56:06.196
ROUND SUPERMARKET

56:07.030 --> 56:12.535
MARI STATIONERY

56:20.543 --> 56:22.796
-Let's go, Seoin Elementary!
-You can do it!

56:22.879 --> 56:25.548
-Go!
-You can do it!

56:26.091 --> 56:28.760
-Let's go, Seoin!
-Seoin Elementary!

56:28.843 --> 56:30.470
Let's go, Eunho Elementary!

56:30.553 --> 56:32.806
-Go, Eunho Elementary!
-Go, Eunho Elementary!

56:32.889 --> 56:34.015
Let's go, Seoin Elementary!

56:34.099 --> 56:36.351
-Go, Seoin Elementary!
-Go, Seoin Elementary!

56:58.998 --> 57:02.043
THE STRONGEST!
SEOIN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL BASEBALL TEAM

57:02.127 --> 57:03.711
SEOIN: 8
EUNHO: 7

57:04.838 --> 57:06.131
-Let's go!
-Ouch.

57:06.214 --> 57:07.215
Hey.

57:10.844 --> 57:12.137
What's wrong?

57:12.220 --> 57:13.346
Did you hurt your shoulder?

57:13.930 --> 57:14.931
Yes.

57:16.433 --> 57:19.352
It hurts too much.
I don't think I can throw anymore.

57:21.729 --> 57:22.730
I-rang, you're up!

57:23.648 --> 57:25.066
M-Me?

57:25.150 --> 57:26.526
Yes, you. Hurry up!

57:28.111 --> 57:29.946
No, I can't…

57:34.159 --> 57:35.160
Dad?

57:37.954 --> 57:39.330
What are you waiting for?

57:39.414 --> 57:40.582
The coach is calling you.

57:42.584 --> 57:44.127
We're going to lose because of me.

57:45.837 --> 57:47.714
No one believes in me.

57:51.176 --> 57:52.427
I don't think I can do it.

57:55.388 --> 57:56.473
Give this to me.

58:00.643 --> 58:06.107
All it takes is one person
to believe in you

58:07.650 --> 58:09.819
to conquer any obstacle.

58:16.201 --> 58:18.536
Even if the whole world
has no faith in you,

58:18.620 --> 58:20.246
you can muster up the courage

58:20.830 --> 58:22.207
for that one person.

58:27.587 --> 58:29.547
I'm that person to you.

58:29.631 --> 58:32.550
No matter what happens,
I'll believe you until the end.

58:33.843 --> 58:35.011
Okay, Dad.

58:35.970 --> 58:36.971
I'll give it a try.

58:43.770 --> 58:45.396
Go, Seoin Elementary!

58:45.480 --> 58:47.148
-Let's go, Seoin!
-Let's go, Seoin!

59:04.040 --> 59:05.208
I can do it.

01:00:07.645 --> 01:00:09.522
What brings you here, Mr. Attorney?

01:00:11.024 --> 01:00:12.400
Why are you here?

01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:16.988
I don't know.

01:00:17.071 --> 01:00:21.200
I went wherever my feet took me
and ended up here.

01:00:26.039 --> 01:00:27.457
Why haven't you…

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:31.044
burned the talisman yet?

01:00:34.005 --> 01:00:35.465
I'm not sure.

01:00:37.133 --> 01:00:38.384
Maybe I wanted to find

01:00:39.677 --> 01:00:43.056
even just a tiny excuse not to burn it.

01:00:46.309 --> 01:00:47.310
But…

01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:51.731
the more I listened to others…

01:00:54.233 --> 01:00:56.027
the more my disappointment grew.

01:01:01.074 --> 01:01:02.116
Now…

01:01:03.326 --> 01:01:05.578
I'm done looking for excuses.

01:01:08.539 --> 01:01:10.249
Despite what others say…

01:01:13.086 --> 01:01:14.337
I've decided

01:01:16.005 --> 01:01:17.590
to believe…

01:01:20.802 --> 01:01:22.428
what I know and remember of you.

01:01:40.947 --> 01:01:42.615
You were born

01:01:44.492 --> 01:01:46.244
on August 15, 1963.

01:01:48.663 --> 01:01:49.831
Your name is Shin Gi-jung.

01:01:55.211 --> 01:01:56.212
You are…

01:01:58.756 --> 01:02:00.258
my father.

01:02:22.280 --> 01:02:23.197
SPECIAL THANKS TO CHOI WON-YOUNG

01:02:44.135 --> 01:02:46.721
Shin Gi-jung died 20 years ago.
Why do you bother with him?

01:02:46.804 --> 01:02:49.015
He's the chairman
of a big law firm named Taebaek.

01:02:49.098 --> 01:02:50.683
We were like brothers.

01:02:50.767 --> 01:02:52.185
-Be careful.
-Don't worry.

01:02:52.268 --> 01:02:54.270
-It can't be him.
-A Four Dragons member?

01:02:54.353 --> 01:02:56.481
-Her name is Han Na-hyun.
-Stop what you're doing now.

01:02:56.564 --> 01:02:59.609
I cannot put my son in danger
trying to resolve my own resentment.

01:02:59.692 --> 01:03:01.611
Burn their talisman,
and the ghost will disappear.

01:03:01.694 --> 01:03:03.571
-What do we do about her?
-I get it, so stop.

01:03:03.654 --> 01:03:04.739
No, I-rang.

01:03:04.822 --> 01:03:06.157
I can't let you go like this.

01:03:06.240 --> 01:03:11.245
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
